ules must be wired together through a shared real state file. REAL-INFRA: The shared artifact is a real file in a temp directory; an in-process fake filesystem is sufficient to catch schema/format mismatches. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) No real OS primitives beyond temp-dir file I/O. (b) No LLM. (c) No chained agentic steps. System rejected: both hooks can be invoked as in-process functions against a shared tmp_path; no subprocess boundary is required for the failure to appear.","test_description":"In a single test with a shared `tmp_path`: (1) invoke the PostToolUse hook's write path with a synthetic PR-create trigger event, pointing state output at `tmp_path`; (2) invoke the pre-tool enforcement hook's read-and-check path, pointing it at the same `tmp_path`; (3) assert the enforcement hook correctly detects a pending review gate (i.e., it would block a subsequent tool call). Additionally assert that an empty `tmp_path` (no state file) does not falsely trigger enforcement.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.04,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10023,"cache_read_input_tokens":3199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":10023},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6f670e3d-77e6-4377-a5f2-0e56fd9effc0","uuid":"701aa512-202d-4d5f-8608-a6dacd4e118a"}
